tColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-star h-3.5 w-3.5 text-[#D4A800] shrink-0\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M11.525 2.295a.53.53 0 0 1 .95 0l2.31 4.679a2.123 2.123 0 0 0 1.595 1.16l5.166.756a.53.53 0 0 1 .294.904l-3.736 3.638a2.123 2.123 0 0 0-.611 1.878l.882 5.14a.53.53 0 0 1-.771.56l-4.618-2.428a2.122 2.122 0 0 0-1.973 0L6.396 21.01a.53.53 0 0 1-.77-.56l.881-5.139a2.122 2.122 0 0 0-.611-1.879L2.16 9.795a.53.53 0 0 1 .294-.906l5.165-.755a2.122 2.122 0 0 0 1.597-1.16z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-xs font-bold text-[#0D2660] whitespace-nowrap\">Indira Gandhi Award 2009</span></div></div></div></div></section><section class=\"section bg-white\"><div class=\"container-site grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 lg:gap-12 items-center\"><div><div class=\"sm:mb-10 md:mb-12 mb-5\"><p class=\"text-xs sm:text-sm font-bold text-[#C8201A] uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">The Region We Serve</p><h2 class=\"text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-[#0D2660] text-balance\">The Abujhmarh Region</h2></div><p class=\"text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4\">Abujhmarh has a tribal population of about 34,000 inhabiting some 233 far-flung villages over a sprawling area of 4,000 sq. km. It is described as a &quot;tangled knot of hills&quot; having an inaccessible terrain that remains absolutely cut off from the rest of the civilized world for about 6 months a year even to this day. The region is about 95 km long from North to South and about 55 km broad from East to West.</p><p class=\"text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4\">The word &quot;Abujhmarh&quot; combines Hindi &#x27;Abujh&#x27; (unknown) and Gondi &#x27;Marh&#x27; (highland). True to its name, it continues to be more or less an unknown and non-surveyed area.</p><p class=\"text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-4\">The habitants — the Abujhmaria or Hill Marias — are a Particularly Vulnerable Tribal Group (PVTG) with slash-and-burn cultivation as their mainstay, very low literacy, and centuries of neglect before the Mission arrived.</p><a class=\"text-[#0D2660] font-semibold hover:underline inline-flex items-center gap-1\" href=\"/about/history\">Read our history <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-arrow-right h-4 w-4\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M5 12h14\"></path><path d=\"m12 5 7 7-7 7\"></path></svg></a></div><div class=\"relative aspect-[4/3] rounded-2xl overflow-hidden border border-blue-100\"><img alt=\"Abujhmarh region served by the Mission\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" class=\"object-cover\" style=\"position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 50vw\" srcSet=\"/_next/image?url=%2Fimages%2Fashrama-2.jpg&amp;w=384&amp;q=75 384w, /_next/image?url=%2Fimages%2Fashrama-2.jpg&amp;w=640&amp;q=75 640w, /_next/image?url=%2Fimages%2Fashrama-2.jpg&amp;w=750&amp;q=75 750w, /_next/image?url=%2Fimages%2Fashrama-2.jpg&amp;w=828&amp;q=75 828w, /_next/image?url=%2Fimages%2Fashrama-2.jpg&amp;w=1080&amp;q=75 1080w, /_next/image?url=%2Fimages%2Fashrama-2.jpg&amp;w=1200&amp;q=75 1200w, /_next/image?url=%2Fimages%2Fashrama-2.jpg&amp;w=1920&amp;q=75 1920w, /_next/image?url=%2Fimages%2Fashrama-2.jpg&amp;w=2048&amp;q=75 2048w, /_next/image?url=%2Fimages%2Fashrama-2.jpg&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75 3840w\" src=\"/_next/image?url=%2Fimages%2Fashrama-2.jpg&amp;w=3840&amp;q=75\"/></div></div></section><section class=\"section section-alt\"><div class=\"container-site\"><div class=\"mb-8 sm:mb-10 md:mb-12 text-center mx-auto max-w-3xl\"><p class=\"text-xs sm:text-sm font-bold text-[#C8201A] uppercase tracking-wider mb-2\">Service to Man is Service to God</p><h2 class=\"text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-[#0D2660] text-balance\">Our Seva Activities</h2><p